<header class='w-full shadow mb-8 print:hidden'>
  <div class='flex w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 py-4 print:hidden'>
    <img src="/favicon.ico" alt="James Ebentier" class='h-9 justify-self-start' />
    <ul class='flex flex-row list-none ml-auto content-center items-center justify-end my-auto'>
      <%# data-nav-target attributes (R4/Decision 6): the single lookup resolveNavTarget()
        queries for both the `g`-prefix page jumps and (a later increment) the COMMAND
        registry's :home/:writing/:projects/:resume. "writing" (not "blog") matches the
        design doc's target IA name, so a future /blog -> /writing route rename requires
        zero keyboard-layer changes. Rails' own root_url/posts_url/projects_url/
        resume_path remain the single source of the actual href -- no URL literal here. %>
      <li class='ml-4'><%= link_to 'Home', root_url, class: current_page?(root_path) ? 'text-primary cursor-default' : 'link link-hover', data: { nav_target: 'home' } %></li>
      <li class='ml-4'><%= link_to 'Blog', posts_url, class: current_page?(posts_path) ? 'text-primary cursor-default' : 'link link-hover', data: { nav_target: 'writing' } %></li>
      <li class='ml-4'><%= link_to 'Projects', projects_url, class: current_page?(projects_url) ? 'text-primary cursor-default' : 'link link-hover', data: { nav_target: 'projects' } %></li>
      <li class='ml-4'><%= link_to 'Resume', resume_path, class: current_page?(resume_url) ? 'text-primary cursor-default' : 'link link-hover', data: { nav_target: 'resume' } %></li>
      <%# Terminal-styled theme switcher (R6). data-theme-picker-target="select" is read
          by app/javascript/controllers/theme_picker_controller.js; the render-blocking
          inline script in application.html.erb's <head> is what applies the visitor's
          stored choice on load (before this control even connects).
          data-keyboard-nav-target="themeSelect" (R5/Decision 4) is a second controller's
          target on this same <select> -- keyboard_nav_controller.js's `t` binding drives
          this exact element via a real `change` event, so theme-picker#change stays the
          one and only code path that ever applies/persists a theme; no parallel logic. %>
      <li class='ml-4 flex items-center gap-1 font-mono text-sm' data-controller='theme-picker'>
        <label for='theme-picker-select' class='sr-only'>Theme</label>
        <span aria-hidden='true' class='text-primary'>&gt;</span>
        <select
          id='theme-picker-select'
          data-theme-picker-target='select'
          data-keyboard-nav-target='themeSelect'
          data-action='theme-picker#change'
          class='select select-ghost select-sm font-mono'
        >
          <option value='light'>light</option>
          <option value='dark'>dark</option>
          <option value='dracula'>dracula</option>
          <option value='nord'>nord</option>
          <option value='gruvbox'>gruvbox</option>
          <option value='catppuccin'>catppuccin</option>
        </select>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</header>
